Package org.openlca.core.model

Class ProcessLink

java.lang.Object
org.openlca.core.model.ProcessLink
All Implemented Interfaces:
Cloneable
@Embeddable public class ProcessLink extends Object implements Cloneable
A process link is a connection between a provider (which can be a process or product system) and a process in a product system.

  • Field Details

    • flowId

      public long flowId
      ID of the flow that is an output of the one process (or the reference flow of a product system) and an input of the other process.

    • providerId

      public long providerId
      ID of the process or product system that is an provider of a product (has a product output) or a waste treatment (has a waste input). The pair (providerId, flowId) is used to index the matrices in the calculation.

    • processId

      public long processId
      ID of the process that has a link to the provider (has a product input or waste output).

    • exchangeId

      public long exchangeId
      ID of the product input or waste output of the process that is linked to a provider. Note that an exchange can be linked to only one provider in a product system but a provider can be linked to multiple exchanges. Also, there can be multiple exchanges in a process with the same flow that are linked to different providers.

    • isSystemLink

      public boolean isSystemLink
      When true, the provider of this link is a product system.
